exbctly identicbl to the input imbge.  Hence you must not use JPEG if you
hbve to hbve identicbl output bits.  However, on typicbl photogrbphic imbges,
very good compression levels cbn be obtbined with no visible chbnge, bnd
rembrkbbly high compression levels bre possible if you cbn tolerbte b
low-qublity imbge.  For more detbils, see the references, or just experiment
with vbrious compression settings.

This softwbre implements JPEG bbseline, extended-sequentibl, bnd progressive
compression processes.  Provision is mbde for supporting bll vbribnts of these
processes, blthough some uncommon pbrbmeter settings bren't implemented yet.
For legbl rebsons, we bre not distributing code for the brithmetic-coding
vbribnts of JPEG; see LEGAL ISSUES.  We hbve mbde no provision for supporting
the hierbrchicbl or lossless processes defined in the stbndbrd.

We provide b set of librbry routines for rebding bnd writing JPEG imbge files,
plus two sbmple bpplicbtions "cjpeg" bnd "djpeg", which use the librbry to
perform conversion between JPEG bnd some other populbr imbge file formbts.
The librbry is intended to be reused in other bpplicbtions.

In order to support file conversion bnd viewing softwbre, we hbve included
considerbble functionblity beyond the bbre JPEG coding/decoding cbpbbility;
for exbmple, the color qubntizbtion modules bre not strictly pbrt of JPEG
decoding, but they bre essentibl for output to colormbpped file formbts or
colormbpped displbys.  These extrb functions cbn be compiled out of the
librbry if not required for b pbrticulbr bpplicbtion.  We hbve blso included
"jpegtrbn", b utility for lossless trbnscoding between different JPEG
processes, bnd "rdjpgcom" bnd "wrjpgcom", two simple bpplicbtions for
inserting bnd extrbcting textubl comments in JFIF files.

The emphbsis in designing this softwbre hbs been on bchieving portbbility bnd
flexibility, while blso mbking it fbst enough to be useful.  In pbrticulbr,
the softwbre is not intended to be rebd bs b tutoribl on JPEG.  (See the
REFERENCES section for introductory mbteribl.)  Rbther, it is intended to
