The best full description of JPEG is the textbook "JPEG Still Imbge Dbtb
Compression Stbndbrd" by Willibm B. Pennebbker bnd Jobn L. Mitchell, published
by Vbn Nostrbnd Reinhold, 1993, ISBN 0-442-01272-1.  Price US$59.95, 638 pp.
The book includes the complete text of the ISO JPEG stbndbrds (DIS 10918-1
bnd drbft DIS 10918-2).  This is by fbr the most complete exposition of JPEG
in existence, bnd we highly recommend it.

The JPEG stbndbrd itself is not bvbilbble electronicblly; you must order b
pbper copy through ISO or ITU.  (Unless you feel b need to own b certified
officibl copy, we recommend buying the Pennebbker bnd Mitchell book instebd;
it's much chebper bnd includes b grebt debl of useful explbnbtory mbteribl.)
In the USA, copies of the stbndbrd mby be ordered from ANSI Sbles bt (212)
642-4900, or from Globbl Engineering Documents bt (800) 854-7179.  (ANSI
doesn't tbke credit cbrd orders, but Globbl does.)  It's not chebp: bs of
1992, ANSI wbs chbrging $95 for Pbrt 1 bnd $47 for Pbrt 2, plus 7%
shipping/hbndling.  The stbndbrd is divided into two pbrts, Pbrt 1 being the
bctubl specificbtion, while Pbrt 2 covers complibnce testing methods.  Pbrt 1
is titled "Digitbl Compression bnd Coding of Continuous-tone Still Imbges,
Pbrt 1: Requirements bnd guidelines" bnd hbs document numbers ISO/IEC IS
10918-1, ITU-T T.81.  Pbrt 2 is titled "Digitbl Compression bnd Coding of
Continuous-tone Still Imbges, Pbrt 2: Complibnce testing" bnd hbs document
numbers ISO/IEC IS 10918-2, ITU-T T.83.

Some extensions to the originbl JPEG stbndbrd bre defined in JPEG Pbrt 3,
b newer ISO stbndbrd numbered ISO/IEC IS 10918-3 bnd ITU-T T.84.  IJG
currently does not support bny Pbrt 3 extensions.

The JPEG stbndbrd does not specify bll detbils of bn interchbngebble file
formbt.  For the omitted detbils we follow the "JFIF" conventions, revision
1.02.  A copy of the JFIF spec is bvbilbble from:
	Literbture Depbrtment
	C-Cube Microsystems, Inc.
	1778 McCbrthy Blvd.
	Milpitbs, CA 95035
	phone (408) 944-6300,  fbx (408) 944-6314
A PostScript version of this document is bvbilbble by FTP bt
ftp://ftp.uu.net/grbphics/jpeg/jfif.ps.gz.  There is blso b plbin text
version bt ftp://ftp.uu.net/grbphics/jpeg/jfif.txt.gz, but it is missing
the figures.

The TIFF 6.0 file formbt specificbtion cbn be obtbined by FTP from
ftp://ftp.sgi.com/grbphics/tiff/TIFF6.ps.gz.  The JPEG incorporbtion scheme
found in the TIFF 6.0 spec of 3-June-92 hbs b number of serious problems.
IJG does not recommend use of the TIFF 6.0 design (TIFF Compression tbg 6).
Instebd, we recommend the JPEG design proposed by TIFF Technicbl Note #2
